## Build sub-menu: fix unreadable "Mapping" stale-indicator badge

Context: In the Build sub-menu (Digital Twin Information →
"Out of sync with last build:" row), the "Mapping" badge that appears
when assignments were modified since the last build rendered as red
text on a solid red background — completely unreadable. Triggered by
the typical "I just updated mapping; the digital twin is now stale"
flow.

Root cause: The badge was declared with the Bootstrap utility classes
``bg-primary bg-opacity-10 text-primary border border-primary`` in
``_query_sync.html``. The project-wide Databricks theme in
``src/front/static/global/css/main.css`` redefines ``.bg-primary``,
``.text-primary`` and ``.border-primary`` to use ``--db-primary``
(``#FF3621``) with ``!important``. The ``!important`` defeats
Bootstrap's ``bg-opacity-*`` modifiers, so what was meant to be a
faint blue tint with darker blue text became solid Databricks red on
solid Databricks red. The neighbouring "Ontology" badge was unaffected
because it uses ``bg-warning`` / ``text-warning`` (not overridden by
the theme).

Fix: Switched the Mapping stale-indicator badge from ``primary`` to
``info`` (cyan/teal). ``bg-info``, ``text-info`` and ``border-info``
are not overridden by the custom theme, so ``bg-opacity-10`` works
again and the badge renders as a readable cyan-on-pale-cyan pill,
visually distinct from the yellow Ontology badge in the same row.

Changes:

1. src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_sync.html
   - ``#syncBadgeAssignmentChanged`` ("Mapping" stale indicator):
     replaced ``bg-primary bg-opacity-10 text-primary border
     border-primary`` with ``bg-info bg-opacity-10 text-info border
     border-info`` so the badge stays readable when the user has just
     modified mapping assignments and the Digital Twin is not yet
     rebuilt.

Modified files:
- src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_sync.html

