## Build sub-menu: stop reporting "Loaded" Graph DB DT when nothing was built

Context: In the same Build sub-menu (Digital Twin Information section,
"Graph DB Digital Twin" card), the existence badge displayed "Loaded"
even on freshly-opened domains where no Digital Twin had ever been
built. The user expectation — sensibly — is that "Loaded" should
correspond to an actual built graph sitting on disk.

Root cause: The readiness probe in
``DigitalTwin.fetch_digital_twin_existence`` computed
``local_lbug_exists`` with a plain ``os.path.exists(local_path)``
check against ``/tmp/ontobricks/<safe_name>.lbug`` (see
``resolve_ladybug_local_path`` →
``GraphSyncService.local_path_for_db``). However Ladybug — via
``LadybugBase._get_connection()`` — auto-creates that on-disk
directory the first time **anything** opens a connection to that
path:

    os.makedirs(os.path.dirname(path), exist_ok=True)
    if not os.path.exists(path):
        self._try_auto_restore(path)
    self._db = lb.Database(path)   # ← creates the directory

Any incidental query (sidebar, readiness probe, schema introspection,
the auto-restore attempt itself) therefore materialises an empty
Kuzu/Ladybug database directory, and ``os.path.exists`` then returns
``True`` forever after — yielding a false-positive "Loaded" badge on
a domain that was never built.

Fix: The readiness probe now gates ``local_lbug_exists`` on
``domain.last_build`` as well, so the badge only flips to "Loaded"
when:
1. The domain has been built at least once (``last_built`` is set),
   AND
2. The local ``.lbug`` directory is actually on disk.

This matches the "Last Built: Never built" copy already shown right
above the card and is consistent with the existing reload-from-
registry flow (registry uploads only happen after a successful build,
so any reloaded local file already corresponds to a non-empty
``last_built``). After a real build, the post-build cache writer at
line 2762 keeps writing the file-on-disk reality unchanged — that
site is correct by construction (it runs only after a successful
build, so both signals are necessarily true).

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/digitaltwin.py
   - ``fetch_digital_twin_existence``: ``local_lbug_exists`` is now
     ``bool(last_built) and os.path.exists(local_path)`` instead of
     a bare ``os.path.exists(local_path)``, eliminating the false
     "Loaded" badge for never-built domains where Ladybug had
     auto-created an empty on-disk database directory as a side
     effect of an earlier query.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/digitaltwin/digitaltwin.py

