## Sidebar: fix "Teams" icon misaligned vs the other entries

Context: In the retractable left sidebar of the Registry page, the
"Teams" entry's icon (``bi-people``) sat slightly off compared to its
neighbours (Browse, Bridges, Schedule, API, Registry Location). The
icon-to-label gap was missing and the glyph appeared visually shifted
within the row. Only Teams was affected because it is the only
sidebar item flagged ``"admin_only": true`` in
``src/front/config/menu_config.json``.

Root cause: The admin-gate in ``src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css``
hides admin-only entries by default and reveals them for admins via
``display: revert``:

    [data-requires-app="admin"]                              { display: none   !important; }
    body[data-app-role="admin"] [data-requires-app="admin"]  { display: revert !important; }

``display: revert`` reverts to the *user-agent default* — bypassing
every author rule. For an ``<a class="nav-link" data-requires-app="admin">``,
that means the Teams entry loses its
``.sidebar-nav .nav-link { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem }``
and falls back to plain ``inline``. Without flex, the ``<i class="bi
bi-people">`` icon container loses ``align-items: center``, the
``gap: 0.5rem`` between icon and label evaporates, and the icon's
fixed-width 20px slot no longer applies the same way — so the glyph
visually misaligns relative to the other (still-flex) sidebar items.

The same trap affects Bootstrap's ``.dropdown-item`` (used in the
navbar admin menu): it normally sets ``display: block``, also wiped
by ``display: revert``.

Fix: Added two targeted "post-revert" rules in ``permissions.css``
right after the admin-reveal block, restoring the proper display per
surface for admin-gated elements:

- ``body[data-app-role="admin"] .sidebar-nav .nav-link[data-requires-app="admin"]``
  → ``display: flex !important`` (re-enables the flex layout that
  centers the icon and applies the icon-to-label gap, matching every
  other sidebar entry).
- ``body[data-app-role="admin"] .dropdown-item[data-requires-app="admin"]``
  → ``display: block !important`` (matches Bootstrap's natural
  dropdown-item layout so admin-only menu items behave like the
  non-gated ones).

Considered but rejected: ``.quick-link-sm`` on the home page also
carries ``data-requires-app="admin"``, but its natural display is
``inline`` (matches the user-agent default for ``<a>``), so
``display: revert`` already produces the correct result — no override
needed.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css
   - Added a documented "post-revert" block restoring
     ``display: flex`` for admin-only sidebar nav-links and
     ``display: block`` for admin-only ``.dropdown-item`` entries, so
     admin-gated UI keeps the same layout as the non-gated siblings.

Modified files:
- src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css

