## Permissions refactor (4 steps): declarative guards + body data-attrs + CSS gating

Context: The permission stack had three pain points — (1) every
write-route in ``dtwin.py`` repeated the same
``role_level(actual) < role_level(ROLE_BUILDER); raise
AuthorizationError`` boilerplate, (2) ``filter_visible_domains`` was
copy-pasted between ``settings.py`` and ``domain.py``, (3)
``permissions.js`` and ``version-check.js`` did per-button JS sweeps
to disable write surfaces for viewers / older versions, fighting with
each new feature that added markup. PermissionService also conflated
app-scoped principals (``list_app_principals``) with workspace-scoped
SCIM users/groups in a single ``_users_cache`` / ``_groups_cache``
pair, silently corrupting lookups when both endpoints were called.

Reorganised the stack into four steps. Each commit is independently
green; together they replace the imperative gating model with a
declarative one (Replace Conditional with Polymorphism + Move Method,
Fowler).

Changes:

Step 1 — quick wins:
1. src/back/objects/registry/PermissionService.py
   Split ``_users_cache``/``_groups_cache`` into ``_app_*`` (used by
   ``list_app_principals``) and ``_workspace_*`` (used by
   ``list_users`` / ``list_groups``). Each pair now has its own
   timestamp; ``clear_principals_cache`` resets all four plus the
   admin and SCIM-membership caches.
2. src/api/routers/internal/_permissions.py (NEW)
   Extracted ``filter_visible_domains`` from the duplicated
   ``_filter_domains_by_user_access`` helpers in ``settings.py`` and
   ``domain.py`` (Extract Function + remove copy-paste).
3. src/api/routers/internal/domain.py
   Removed the local ``_filter_domains_by_user_access`` and routed
   ``list_domains`` through ``filter_visible_domains``.
4. src/api/routers/internal/settings.py
   Same — dropped the duplicated helper, now imports from
   ``_permissions``.

Step 2 — declarative route guards:
5. src/back/objects/registry/guards.py (NEW)
   ``require(min_role, *, scope='app'|'domain')`` factory returning a
   FastAPI ``Depends`` that reads ``request.state.user_role`` /
   ``user_domain_role`` and raises ``AuthorizationError`` below the
   minimum. Domain scope falls back to the app role to mirror the
   middleware's resolution order.
6. src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py
   Re-exported ``require`` so handlers do
   ``from back.objects.registry import require``.
7. src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py
   Replaced three inline ``role_level(...) < ROLE_BUILDER`` blocks
   in ``start_triplestore_sync``, ``reload_graph_from_registry``,
   ``drop_snapshot`` with
   ``dependencies=[Depends(require(ROLE_BUILDER, scope='domain'))]``.
8. src/api/routers/internal/settings.py
   Same pattern for the admin-only settings / permission management
   endpoints.

Step 3 — server-injected permissions on <body>:
9. src/front/fastapi/dependencies.py
   Registered ``get_user_role`` / ``get_user_domain_role`` /
   ``is_app_mode`` Jinja globals so templates can render the caller's
   resolved roles without a JS round-trip.
10. src/front/templates/base.html
    ``<body>`` now carries ``data-app-role`` / ``data-domain-role`` /
    ``data-app-mode``. Replaced the ``admin-only-nav`` +
    ``style="display:none"`` pattern (toggled by JS) with
    ``data-requires-app="admin"`` (gated by CSS, see Step 4).
11. src/front/static/global/js/permissions.js (NEW)
    Reads the body data-attrs once at parse time, exposes a frozen
    ``window.OB.permissions`` namespace (``hasAppRole`` /
    ``hasDomainRole`` mirroring the backend ``role_level``), stamps
    ``body.role-viewer`` for non-admin viewers, installs the shared
    capture-phase contextmenu blocker for D3/Canvas surfaces, and
    renders the navbar role pill. Loaded **first** so every other
    script can read ``window.OB.permissions`` synchronously.
12. src/front/templates/partials/layout/_sidebar_nav.html
13. src/front/templates/home.html
    Same ``admin-only-nav`` → ``data-requires-app="admin"``
    migration.

Step 4 — declarative CSS gating:
14. src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css (NEW)
    Single source of truth for role / version gating. App-role gates
    use ``[data-requires-app="admin"]``; domain-role gates use
    ``[data-requires="builder"|"editor"]``;
    ``body:is(.read-only-version, .role-viewer)`` neutralises every
    write surface (~40 selectors covering Domain → Metadata,
    Documents, Ontology imports, Mapping designer, Business Views,
    Data Quality, Save Domain, generic form fields). Loaded **last**
    so its ``!important`` gates beat per-component rules.
15. src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js
    Shrunk from ~535 lines to ~50: the version-status round-trip
    just adds ``read-only-version`` to <body> and reuses the same
    CSS gates as viewer mode (and ``permissions.js``'s contextmenu
    blocker). The 13 helpers that disabled controls one by one are
    gone.
16. src/front/static/global/js/navbar.js,
    src/front/static/registry/js/registry.js,
    src/front/static/global/js/breadcrumb.js,
    src/front/static/global/js/ontology-core.js,
    src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js,
    src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-{axioms,entities,
    relationships,shared-panels,swrl}.js
    Cleaned up references to the removed ``admin-only-nav`` /
    ``disableEditingForInactiveVersion`` paths and routed remaining
    role checks through ``window.OB.permissions``.
17. src/front/static/global/css/{components,main,mapping,sidebar-layout}.css,
    src/front/static/global/ontoviz/css/{ontoviz,ontoviz-ui}.css
    Adjusted selectors so OntoViz toolbars and mapping/sidebar
    write controls compose cleanly with the new
    ``:is(.read-only-version, .role-viewer)`` gates.

Tests:
18. tests/test_route_guards.py (NEW)
    27 cases — factory validation, comparison logic against
    hand-rolled requests, end-to-end via FastAPI ``TestClient`` for
    both ``app`` and ``domain`` scopes, AuthorizationError → 403
    surface check.
19. tests/test_permissions.py
    Extended cache-split coverage: ``clear_principals_cache``
    drops every relevant cache; ``list_app_principals`` and
    ``list_users`` no longer share state.

Docs:
20. docs/data-access.md (NEW)
    Engine map describing which wrapper (REST / GraphQL / SPARQL /
    Spark SQL / Cypher) every UI / MCP / Chat feature uses.
    Surfaced via ``docs/sphinx/index.rst`` and the in-app Help
    Center (``src/api/routers/internal/help.py:_DOC_CATEGORIES``,
    ``src/front/templates/partials/layout/help_modal.html``).
21. docs/README.md, docs/sphinx/index.rst,
    docs/sphinx/guides/data-access.md
    Wired the new data-access guide into both the file index and
    the Sphinx toctree.

